		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>Rime Snap, Rk II<br />
<br />
1183 mana<br />
0 cast 8.25 recast -50 CR<br />
5186 damage<br />
Chill: 25% chance at +1121 damage on next nuke<br />
<br />
So, pure-cold instants while kiting, assuming average +60% damage from crits/foci:<br />
<br />
(5186 + .25*1121) * 1.6 / 8.25 = 1060 DPS<br />
Assuming 30% mana savings:<br />
(5186 + .25*1121) * 1.6 / (1183*.7) = 10.6 damage per mana<br />
<br />
Cold Snap, Rk II (current)<br />
1048 mana<br />
4399 damage<br />
0 cast, 6 recast, -50 CR<br />
Ignore chill effect.<br />
<br />
1106.4 DPS<br />
9.6 damage per mana<br />
<br />
Cold Snap, Rk II (pre-nerf)<br />
4399 damage<br />
978 mana<br />
1173.1 DPS<br />
10.3 damage per mana<br />
<br />
So the result: the new instants are <b>more efficient</b> than the pre-nerf instants.  They do slightly less DPS if all you do is chain-cast the instant.<br />
<br />
However, if you cast an instant, then pause 3/4 of a second to cast a non-instant...<br />
<br />
You can easily fit a Chaos Conflagaration (for example) during the recast.<br />
<br />
That boosts your damage per 8.25 second cycle up by another +3613.6<br />
<br />
So, instant + fast cast nuke:<br />
(5186 + .25*1121 + 2258.5) * 1.6 / 8.25 = 1498.1 DPS<br />
Assuming 30% mana savings:<br />
(5186 + .25*1121 + 2258.5) * 1.6 / ((1183+382)*.7) = 11.3 damage per mana<br />
<br />
And voila -- 30% upgrade in kiting DPS and a boost in efficiency from simply swapping in a fast-cast efficient nuke during the downtime.  It does mean you have to pause every 8 seconds for less than a second.<br />
<br />
I'm betting with the new Ethereals (doing 9500 damage) an instant/big nuke pattern will produce more DPS than old instant-chaining at a better efficiency.<br />
<br />
...<br />
<br />
This needs more work, and problems will probably boil out post-live.<br />
<br />
But this actually makes a wizard <b>better</b> at kiting than they where before the first instant nerf.  A good 25% boost in DPS and a smaller boost in efficiency.<br />
<br />
One can't use a horse to kite this way, however.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
