		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>If the instants had got the normal revamp (they got slightly better efficiency upgrades), they would look like this chaining rank 3s with end game gear. <br />
<br />
1368 Mana, 5603 Damage<br />
<br />
So assuming you have a bard so both instants would be focused, the average damage is basically:<br />
<br />
2 * (5603 + 5603 * 180% * 28% + 5603 * 35% / 2 + 5603 * 70% / 2) = ~22737 damage<br />
<br />
22737 / 6 = 3789.5 DPS<br />
<br />
22737/ (1368 * 2) = 8.31 DPM ignoring mana preservation effects<br />
<br />
<br />
Casting FF/EI in combination yields:<br />
<br />
FF  = (5603 + 5603 * 180% * 28% + 5603 * 35% / 2 + 5603 * 70% / 2)  = ~11368<br />
Since FF has a recourse that affects the base damage of the next nuke, we use 10264 + 1121 * 25% for the base damage of EI.<br />
<br />
 (10544.25 + 10544.25 * 180% * 28% + 10544.25 * 35% / 2 + 10544.25 * 70% / 2) = ~21394<br />
<br />
= 11368 + 21394 = ~32762<br />
<br />
32762 / 8 = 4095.25 DPS<br />
<br />
32762 / ( 1278 + 2496) = 8.68 DPM ignoring mana preservation effects<br />
<br />
If you want to factor in mana resurgence, thats about 1973 damage per nuke on average, so:<br />
<br />
22737 + 1973 + 1973 = 26683 / 6 = 4447.17 DPS<br />
<br />
32762 + 1973 + 1973 = 36708 / 8 = 4588.5 DPS<br />
<br />
If you don't have a bard, the difference is even bigger of course since the second case is all the same resist instead of 2. I'm not totally happy with all the numbers on the spells at the moment, but this is where they are right now.<br />
<br />
<br />
There have been other numbers posted by people, I'm sure they will show up here as the day goes on as well.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
