<br />
In addition to what Gavrilo mentioned..<br />
<br />
It's hard to balance us overall since we have access to the best &quot;weapons&quot; (i.e. spells) from the start with the only limiting factor being the amount of mana each individual has.  When TSS hit, wizards were able to push out insane amounts of dps in group settings.  This produced a collective moan from the community that brought us into the limelight for the wrong reasons.<br />
<br />
Tangent aside, we have the best weapons available from the get-go, melee will need to wait to receive them.  If they out-parse us from the start, there is nowhere for them to go but up while we stay the same.  As it stands, I hope that another look is taken at the current set-up though I'd like to see some numbers first-hand before making a final decision.<br />
<br />
Also, when was the last time spells from a previous expansion were changed to reflect an upcoming one?  Why were those changes warranted in this case?</div>
	</td>
